{"title":"Review: Rapha Pro Team & Explore Winter clothing wrap up","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/05/review-rapha-winter-clothing-wrap-up/","date":1614963064000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span>This winter has been brutal, with record cold temps and crazy weather patterns. If you were brave enough to get outside and ride – you know a good winter kit goes a long way. Rapha’s newest winter offerings came to us at the perfect time, just as the snow was falling and the wind was howling.&nbsp;</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter jacket full\" width=\"1280\" height=\"981\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-297x228.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-800x613.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-120x92.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-768x589.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-696x533.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-1068x819.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-548x420.jpeg 548w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-80x60.jpeg 80w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-297x228.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-800x613.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-120x92.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-768x589.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-696x533.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-1068x819.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-548x420.jpeg 548w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7875-80x60.jpeg 80w\"></a></p><p><span>A good winter jacket can be the keystone of a long-ride winter training day. Something that won’t get clammy or overheat – it’s like you need the jacket to react to your body. That’s what the Rapha Pro Team Winter jacket does, it’s warm where you need it and vented where you don’t. </span><span>The construction and fabrication of the jacket are exquisite. The materials and attention to detail show this piece can go the long haul and will be around for winters to come.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing Jacket detail text\" width=\"1280\" height=\"855\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-800x534.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-120x80.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-768x513.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-696x465.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-1068x713.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-629x420.jpeg 629w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-800x534.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-120x80.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-768x513.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-696x465.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-1068x713.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7887-629x420.jpeg 629w\"></a></p><p><span>The front of the jacket is wind and waterproof. In contrast, the sides and rear are breathable brushed fleece to help regulate the body temperature. The collar isn’t too high and fits at just the right height to zip fully without a tight feeling on the bike.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing full kit riding\" width=\"1280\" height=\"991\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-297x230.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-800x619.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-120x93.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-768x595.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-696x539.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-1068x827.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-542x420.jpeg 542w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-297x230.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-800x619.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-120x93.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-768x595.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-696x539.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-1068x827.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7857-542x420.jpeg 542w\"></a></p><p><span>At first, the jacket seemed too short but on the bike, I noted the lack of bulk quickly. </span><span>There are no crazy pocket designs or out-of-the-box elements, just super solid construction and quality components. All zippers are YKK Vislon and operate with ease. Something that is very nice when you’re trying to operate a zipper with bulky gloves while riding. The rear pockets are double layered with added reinforcement for constant winter use.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing Jacket back full\" width=\"1280\" height=\"801\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-297x186.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-800x501.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-120x75.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-768x481.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-696x436.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-1068x668.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-671x420.jpeg 671w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-297x186.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-800x501.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-120x75.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-768x481.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-696x436.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-1068x668.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7876-671x420.jpeg 671w\"></a></p><p><span>ON the bottom of the jacket is a leg gripper-like material that keeps the piece in place. The super white Rapha logos stand out nicely on the forest green fabric and double reflective elements in the rear of the jacket. Other reflective pieces are on the bicep and cuff. Disguised in Rapha’s six-bar logo this accentuates the design of the jacket while giving it some extra safety features.&nbsp;</span><span>For super cold days, this is my go-to jacket. Most of my winter riding has been on the trails or less-traveled roads and this piece ate the cold headwinds for breakfast. The thick winterproof front kept me warm on the coldest rides and I never overheated.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing Jacket side\" width=\"1280\" height=\"855\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-800x534.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-120x80.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-768x513.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-696x465.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-1068x713.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-629x420.jpeg 629w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-800x534.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-120x80.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-768x513.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-696x465.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-1068x713.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7877-629x420.jpeg 629w\"></a></p><p><span>I attribute the jacket’s acclimatization to the sides’ open design and back paired with micro-wicking brushed fleece on the front. The pockets are easy to get to in a hurry and have a small elastic band to keep items and bottles safe. The cuffs are tight and seemed too tight at first but on the open road, I quickly noticed that no air found its way in. </span><span>I would have liked to see a zipper pocket in the rear like other winter jackets.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7881.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7881.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing Jacket detail pocket\" width=\"1280\" height=\"855\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_788