et but the thin mesh inner can rip if you’re storing keys or something with an unfinished edge.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span>All in all, this is my go-to winter jacket, and I do believe it’s worth the money. Just make sure you follow the washing instructions to keep the reflective elements intact and shrinkage at a minimum.&nbsp;</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing full kit\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-297x297.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-800x800.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-120x120.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-768x768.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-696x696.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-1068x1068.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-420x420.jpeg 420w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-297x297.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-800x800.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-120x120.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-768x768.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-696x696.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-1068x1068.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7872-420x420.jpeg 420w\"></a></p><p><span><a href=\"https://www.rapha.cc/us/en_US/shop/mens-pro-team-winter-jacket/product/PJW01XXBGSSML\">Rapha Pro Team Winter Jacket</a> comes in Green/Dark Green (tested), Purple/Dark Navy, and Black/White.&nbsp;</span><span>Available in sizes X-Small to XX-Large – </span><span>Price: $250</span></p><h2><span>Rapha Explore Winter Tights&nbsp;</span></h2><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880.jpeg\"><img loading=\"eager\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880.jpeg?ezimgfmt=ng%3Awebp%2Fngcb8%2Frs%3Adevice%2Frscb8-1\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing explore tights pocket zipper\" width=\"855\" height=\"1280\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880.jpeg 855w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880-200x300.jpeg 200w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880-800x1198.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880-80x120.jpeg 80w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880-768x1150.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880-696x1042.jpeg 696w, https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7880-281x420.jpeg 281w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 855px) 100vw, 855px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\"></a></p><p><span>Some of us are nearing the end of winter (fingers crossed) but these garments transcend a traditional winter range. The tights are perfect for temperatures ranging from 40 deg down to the single digits. The breathability and wicking characteristics of the brushed fabric allow the bib tights to dry quickly. Rather than going for a full wind/waterproof front, Rapha opted for a DWR coating to reduce bulk.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing explore tights strap material\" width=\"855\" height=\"1280\" sizes=\"(max-width: 855px) 100vw, 855px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886.jpeg 855w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-200x300.jpeg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-800x1198.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-80x120.jpeg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-768x1150.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-696x1042.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-281x420.jpeg 281w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886.jpeg 855w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-200x300.jpeg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-800x1198.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-80x120.jpeg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-768x1150.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-696x1042.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7886-281x420.jpeg 281w\"></a></p><p><span>The DWR coating keeps out the elements and the warmth inside. I like the ease of movement with these bib tights. Some with a wind front outer have less movement and are cut with an articulated knee. Resulting in lots of stitching to abrade and annoy.&nbsp; </span><span>If you like the Rapha Crago Bib, chances are you’re gonna love this tight. It’s covered in pockets, some thin, some waterproof, and zippered. All the pockets are unnoticeable on the bike and don’t affect the fit of tight. The pockets I use the most are the non-zip mid-thigh pocket and the zippered rear pocket.</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing Jacket back\" width=\"1280\" height=\"855\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-800x534.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-120x80.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-768x513.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-696x465.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-1068x713.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-629x420.jpeg 629w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883.jpeg 1280w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-297x198.jpeg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-800x534.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-120x80.jpeg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-768x513.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-696x465.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-1068x713.jpeg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7883-629x420.jpeg 629w\"></a></p><p><span>One pocket for grabbing quick food, the other for car keys or what have you. As most who ride long days in adverse weather know – pockets are a premium when you’re caring extra bottles and extra supplies for the ride.</span></p><p><span>A top-notch winter tight is nothing without a ride all day chamois and the Rapha Winter Tight delivers. I’m a fan of the Rapha chamois, they never deviate, I know I’m getting something predictable. The chamois is a two-piece design, part of the Rapha Brevet line. The sculpted shape feels natural on the bike and covers completely no matter what position you’re riding in. I can spend hours in this tight without posterior discomfort – something that is rare for me on long low-intensity winter rides.&nbsp;</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing explore tights Rear reflective\" width=\"893\" height=\"1280\" sizes=\"(max-width: 893px) 100vw, 893px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885.jpeg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885.jpeg 893w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-209x300.jpeg 209w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-800x1147.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-84x120.jpeg 84w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-768x1101.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-696x998.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-293x420.jpeg 293w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885.jpeg 893w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-209x300.jpeg 209w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-800x1147.jpeg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-84x120.jpeg 84w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-768x1101.jpeg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-696x998.jpeg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7885-293x420.jpeg 293w\"></a></p><p><span>My favorite element of the bib is the reflective flair. If you’re outside riding in this weather chances are it’s in a low-light situation. Half of the entire rear leg is reflective; the material and added elements. Though the black fabric isn’t great for visibility in low light, the reflective elements help propel this bib into a safer category. </span><span>$325 is a hefty asking price for a cycling garment. If you spend a lot of time riding outside in the winter and take your comfort as seriously as your exploring, Rapha’s Explore Winter Tight should be on your shortlist.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7882.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/IMG_7882.jpeg\" alt=\"Rapha Winter clothing explore tights pocket\" width=\"855\" height=\"1280\" sizes=\"(max-width: 855px) 100vw, 855px\" ezi